snippet.textDisplay:
Should we forget the blood of our people flown in 1947  for others' zeal? We didn't wish for a partition, our people didn't start the blood fest. Then why are we doomed to feel guilty and cry? Those slain innocents who didn't want to leave their ancestral homes, what crime did they commit? I'm sorry my heart cannot forget the miseries, tears, and blood of my innocent people. 
The longing for each other and hatred for each other has become our eternal hell and there won't be an escape, ever.
